comments.body: @kevinreiss I'm tagging you in this issue.
We decided to use the string 'Full Text' if there is no title in the electronic_portfolio_s.

In this example: https://catalog.princeton.edu/catalog/9996338243506421 the available online section appears empty because the electronic_portfolio url of the sibling record https://catalog.princeton.edu/catalog/9995002873506421/raw does not include a title. It is empty. What are we doing when the title is empty? Do we display the url or a part of it?
The 951 $8 indicates that the sibling_record is an alma record. 
I will review with @mzelesky the 856 of the sibling record to make sure it is indexed as expected.

Following up on this comment https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata/pull/1579#issuecomment-895655636
We reviewed with @mzelesky various alma records and different electronic portfolios. A new issue is that there are active portfolios but with no title. The reason is that the existing electronic_portfolio_s logic depends only in an existing collection. We should update the logic with a new condition for cases where the portfolio is part of a book and not a collection. I will open a different issue for that. https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata/issues/1589

With the change in #1589 we have 'Full Text' as a title for electronic portfolios that are not part of a collection.:

pudl-migration.title: Ivan Susanin (UPenn item) not migrated to Figgy from PUDL. More information needed

comments.body:
From @jpstroop : The long and short of it is that the collected critical/urtext/etc. works of Russian composers are hard to get...In 2006 a musicology grad student needed this and we did not have a copy, nor could we get one loaned to us long-term, and it was needed for his dissertation. It was decided to do high-res scan while we had it.  The music librarian at Penn, Dick Griscom, who just retired last year, gave us a verbal OK to put it up on our site.

Way forward: in order to migrate the structural metadata, we need a MARC record to ingest to in figgy.  @kelea99 sent request to cataloging issues with links to the PUDL item, the record at UPenn for the complete work, and search results for records describing the items we digitized here at PUL (T.12 a, b, suppl)*.  one record is available @cwulfman will migrate item/structure to figgy and it will be made available via the online catalog.

*Brittany from Mendel is being kept in the loop and will also look for record examples that might help cataloging. 


PUDL: http://pudl.princeton.edu/objects/w9505053d

UPenn complete work: https://franklin.library.upenn.edu/catalog/FRANKLIN_991827123503681

Bit that we have (examples from WorldCat): https://www.worldcat.org/title/ivan-susanin/oclc/474858008&referer=brief_results
just confirmed: Brittany agrees. She would use the example from world cat above for the bit we have here.
